This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with predicting 3D shape from 2D images. It may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves generating 3D point clouds. The use of a neural network for prediction suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a dataset and validation metrics suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
